Detailed Description

Sorted, exclusive, self-exanding array of data blobs.

Description:

Use this object and it's functions to maintain a sorted array of data "blobs". It's implemented as an array of void pointers and the user must provide the size of the blobs and a comparison function. The array is self expanding and maintains a sorted, unique, set of the blobs integers. The array does not automatically shrink, but fc_squeezeSortedBlobArray() can be used to minimize memory usage.
